Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.40,0:01:38.47,Top,,0,0,0,,This time, the second form
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.47,0:01:42.17,Top,,0,0,0,,had prepared a class full of cats, \Nto the consternation of Miss Kennedy who hates cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.17,0:01:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They've pushed her to the point \Nof quitting {her job at }St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.04,0:01:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But Miss Kennedy proved \Nthe strength of her spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.34,0:01:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when she slapped the second form girl \Nwho called Catherine a thief! {??? maybe it's about the actual strength of the slap}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.14,0:01:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And when she said that being considerate to others is the most important thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.58,0:01:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone was moved to tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.65,0:02:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, we convinced \NMiss Kennedy not to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.52,0:02:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.33,0:02:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, have you heard, people?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.37,0:02:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Galliano's Circus has come to town!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.92,0:02:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.84,0:02:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Galliano's Circus is famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.41,0:02:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, I wanna see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.88,0:02:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.91,0:02:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A circus, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.75,0:02:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't wait to see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.01,0:02:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in awe of it, truly! {/really admire}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My... {?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see a poster in the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! And now I wanna go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.89,0:02:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, the circus talk \Ncan wait until after class.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.86,0:02:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.03,0:02:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I do have this to add, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.10,0:02:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress decided that two forms \Nwill take turns going to the circus each evening. {meaning every night some two forms would go to see it, say 1st and 2nd tonight, 3rd and 4th tomorrow}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.57,0:02:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice! How fortunate! {lit: Lucky!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.05,0:03:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go see the poster later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.09,0:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.12,0:03:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, here it is! {/found it}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Galliano's Circus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.82,0:03:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is famous for its flying trapeze performances.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And their star performer \Nis a young man about our age! {lol, no, this doesn't work, he's clearly older than ten which is the girl's age in the anime, unlike 14 in the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.28,0:03:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Their star turn is a flying trapeze artist. \NIt should be marvellous! {lit: I admire it}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.09,0:03:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wanna go and see their tent?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.77,0:03:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's take a peek!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we'll meet that boy there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, better forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.49,0:03:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's their pride—a star, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.46,0:03:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Not a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.71,0:04:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, there're the clowns!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.38,0:04:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.20,0:04:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Look there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.36,0:04:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.01,0:04:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, are you girls the students from St. Clare's?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:05:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The troupe leader said your whole school \Nwill be coming to see us, that's how.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.96,0:05:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Each evening, two forms will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.90,0:05:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our form's turn is this Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.37,0:05:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.08,0:05:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... I'm Jimmy Brown. \NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.18,0:05:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.68,0:05:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand if you're \Ntalking all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.90,0:05:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel, nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm her twin sister Pat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.37,0:05:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you two really are alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.82,0:05:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my turn! {????}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.23,0:05:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm Janet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.76,0:05:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Kathleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.82,0:05:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.34,0:05:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jimmy! \NC'mere for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! Will be there in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.44,0:05:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Wednesday, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.67,0:05:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If I spot you girls in the crowd, \NI'll make a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{????}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.41,0:06:02.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.70,0:06:04.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,When I see Jimmy on Wednesday...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.87,0:06:07.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,I should bring him a gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.17,0:06:09.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll be the only one with a gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if I can find \Nsomething suitable to gift to him... Ah! {think she means "appropriate to his trade/personality"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.88,0:06:24.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is it. This will be my gift for Jimmy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those keychains are all the rage right now. {keyholder - think what she bought was closer to a trinket tho?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.92,0:06:39.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,Jimmy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:43.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Jimmy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:47.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,Jimmy Brown, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:52.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,Jimmy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.28,0:06:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Isabel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, what is the matter with you? {lit: what's so funny}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.35,0:07:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.85,0:07:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever broke the glass \Nin this classroom must own up
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,before the last lesson of the day is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.05,0:07:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.99,0:07:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But Miss Roberts, I already asked all the girls, \Nand the culprit really isn't in our class.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. However, if the culprit is not found...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.95,0:07:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.00,0:07:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The window panes here are a special order. {?? dunno how that works}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can't establish who did it, Headmistress \Nwill make it a collective responsibility. {lit: will make everyone pay the compensation}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Though it still won’t be enough \Nto cover the full cost, you’ll have to forfeit {??????? lit: although the full amount is impossible - how fucking expensive a single glass pane can be dawg?? maybe she means "it'd be impoissible to make each one of you pay the full amount"??}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.71,0:08:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the twenty-shilling circus entrance fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.15,0:08:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean we can't go \Nto the circus tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.46,0:08:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In such cases, it is the school's duty \Nto have everyone take collective responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.75,0:08:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start the lesson now. \NPlease open page 42.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.82,0:08:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And they left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.09,0:08:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.35,0:08:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We definitely didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.72,0:08:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we be punished?! {that's a good fucking question girl, what the fuck, like it's their class so they must pay for someone else damaging it? Did their scriptwriter kill himself after episode 6 or something? It doesn't make sense in the book until a few chapters later either: "It was one of the second form,” she said. “Apparently the ball bounced in here, the girl rushed for it, tried to catch it, and it was knocked on to the window, which broke." - like how the fuck are we supposed to know it was the first form's classroom??}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.66,0:08:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts explained it already. \NThat's how it's always done at our school. {lit: a place such as school is that kind of place}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.10,0:08:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, people! \NAre you just gonna suck it up like that? {lit: keep this up and retreat/withdraw}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.27,0:08:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, there are two circus shows each evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.94,0:09:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One at 6.30 to 8.30 \Nand the second at 8.45 to 10.45.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying we could still \Ngo see that later one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.68,0:09:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.78,0:09:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But the curfew’s at ten o’clock.  \NWe shan’t be able to get back by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the dorm entrances \Nwill be closed by then! {lit is "all the doors" but I think she only means doors to the street}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.12,0:09:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have just a plan for that. \NYou know there are ladders in the shed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.46,0:09:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use that ladder to enter the dorm \Nthrough the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just make sure it's not locked. {the window}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.53,0:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all nice, \Nbut what if you get spotted? {/what will we do if they find us}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They might expel you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.87,0:09:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we just need to make sure \Nwe don't get spotted. Who's with me? Here! {???}{last part is "people who want to go [place your hand on mine to show it], here"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.47,0:09:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.77,0:09:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.94,0:09:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.78,0:09:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What, no one else is coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.98,0:09:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then it's the four of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.18,0:09:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.45,0:09:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, you're going too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.41,0:09:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I've already promised \NI would come today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.34,0:09:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.59,0:09:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom... that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.70,0:09:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? {ne? - implying "you know, right?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to leave the campus unnoticed. {??????? lit: if we go along (a river, coast, railway, etc.); on (e.g. a street) the [school] grounds, not get spotted - could be something like "if we stick close to the school grounds we won't get spotted??" but what's the point, they'd have to leave it anyway, also sounds like they have other options, as in "let's go through the campus, we won't get noticed that way" but what other options there may be???}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.04,0:10:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid using any light. {???? lit: light is no good - they can't possibly have headlights on their bicycles and we don't see any, so it's most likely "avoid being in the light" but that's one hell of a stretch; also they head "lamps" in the book but we don't see any?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.70,0:10:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that? {dare - meaning "whose bicycle is making that creaking"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.78,0:10:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.91,0:10:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do something about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.96,0:10:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful, Kath!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry... {/okay...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.02,0:10:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't wanna be late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.95,0:10:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:51.02,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.23,0:11:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can stop us now. {lit: without anyone getting in the way - meaning "we don't have to be afraid of running into someone we know anymore"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.77,0:11:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finally at the circus, \Nand we'll see Jimmy again! {lit: we'll get to see the circus [performance] and meet jimmy}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.25,0:11:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.12,0:11:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're lucky to find these empty seats!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.39,0:11:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.42,0:11:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,True!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But will Jimmy really be able to spot us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.96,0:11:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need to cheer him on loudly enough. {lit: from here, shouting in loud voice is enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.66,0:11:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.53,0:11:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"Jimmy!"—like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.96,0:11:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.93,0:11:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.57,0:11:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Isabel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.27,0:11:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.32,0:11:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Look—Headmistress is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.74,0:11:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.88,0:11:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, we can't afford being loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did she have to come now, of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.44,0:11:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.78,0:12:30.68,Top,,0,0,0,,And now, a lion tamer's show! {?????? only confidently hear "lion" there}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:38.79,Top,,0,0,0,,Will he be able to guide this golden lion \Nthrough the ring of fire successfully? {???? can't really hear what kind of lion}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.22,0:12:46.93,Top,,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.93,0:12:51.87,Top,,0,0,0,,And now, Jimmy Brown's \NAmazing Flying Trapeze Show begins!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.73,0:13:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.29,0:13:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be surprised how boisterous Kathleen can be in situations like this. {??}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.76,0:13:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.53,0:13:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't judge a book by its cover, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.48,0:13:41.62,Top,,0,0,0,,And now, at last, Jimmy’s trump card—\Nthe double mid-air somersault!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.81,0:14:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's leave before Headmistress does.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.11,0:14:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.19,0:14:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right! \NI still need to say my goodbyes to Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.82,0:14:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.76,0:14:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.06,0:14:19.48,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But where could he be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.93,0:14:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.44,0:14:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where Jimmy's dressing room is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the yellow trailer up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.87,0:14:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.38,0:14:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{mommo - idk what this interjection means, probably "oh geez/gimme a break/can't believe it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.66,0:14:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Headmistress all right! {-ttara = can't believe [that person]}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.95,0:15:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That Hilary...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.02,0:15:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you trust her for anything? {lit: even tho I told her so much}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.09,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe try another window?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.27,0:15:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.70,0:15:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.71,0:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up with all four of you sneezing today?\NAre you girls okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps something did happen, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.59,0:16:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll never grow up into proper ladies \Nif you keep sneezing non-stop in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, I'm still very happy today. \NAnd I have great news for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.32,0:16:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who broke \Nthe window pane owned up to it. {/appeared}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a second form girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.24,0:16:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,While playing with a lacrosse ball, she broke the glass \Nin this classroom, and chose to run away at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But she was going to confess \Nat the end of that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, due to a bad attack of flu, \Nshe was suddenly bedridden with fever. {lit: developed bad fever and ended up collapsing}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.19,0:16:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So she just couldn't confess in time? {lit: she was late to confess?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.31,0:16:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.46,0:16:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll still be able to go to the circus?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.98,0:16:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still performing today!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.43,0:16:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.48,0:16:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress also said that their flying trapeze program is exceptional, so make sure to watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.35,0:17:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.95,0:17:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To make up for upsetting you so much earlier, \Nshe will treat you to tea with cakes in the town first. {today}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.87,0:17:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.00,0:17:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Kathleen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.46,0:17:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.94,0:17:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,don't feel so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.28,0:17:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.46,0:17:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.70,0:17:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Kathleen? \NMy, what awful fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts, Janet too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.12,0:17:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel with Pat too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.34,0:17:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know yet if it's just \Na bad case of fever, or something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, they’ll have to miss \Ntoday’s circus outing, won’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.36,0:17:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that is absolutely out of question!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.70,0:17:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for them, but it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, they're the most animated \Nof our students... {to be in high spirits; to be full of vigor}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.83,0:18:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, they have been perfect bricks about all this—\Nnot a grumble, not one word of complaint. {book}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's gotten into them. {lit: I wonder what chance; stroke of luck; (curious) turn of events it was - dunno if it's a pun on kaze (cold) or not}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.45,0:18:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.44,0:18:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder whose performance \Nthey're watching now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the clowns...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.91,0:18:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the lion tamer's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.40,0:18:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably not the flying trapeze yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.92,0:18:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, if we didn't catch a cold, \Nwould we have gone today anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.18,0:18:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I now feel awfully mean for going to see it \Nlast night without everyone else... {damatte = silently/quietly - dunno what she means since they obviously invited everyone else}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But we invited them all right... {lit : I don't think I went damatte - ?? here I have even less idea what she means by "quietly", probably it's just their word for "sneakily"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.60,0:18:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, we shouldn't have gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.02,0:18:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's no use thinking about all that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But the last night in town \Nis the best time to see the circus. {lit: for circus, the last night is the most interesting}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.86,0:18:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yeah...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.89,0:18:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a fool... {yappari = after all...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.66,0:18:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.10,0:19:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Any developments?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.32,0:19:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it seems their fever has subsided.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.04,0:19:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At least they didn't catch a flu, it seems. {lit: it seems it wasn't a bad cold}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought them some \Nof the chocolate cakes we had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.40,0:20:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My, they should be properly delighted!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But not just now—\Nthey're fast asleep, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.87,0:20:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't forget about us, Miss Roberts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.45,0:20:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.75,0:20:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I love those chocolate cakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.55,0:20:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind if we do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.80,0:20:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness! Are you sure you should \Nget out of bed already?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, as long as there're cakes! {?????}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems their illness \Nhas magically disappeared already! {lit: flew away somewhere}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.22,0:20:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all the medicine we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.86,0:20:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.53,0:20:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The circus truly was jolly fun. \NI so wish you could've seen it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts, the clowns' performance \Nwas only second to the flying trapeze, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.37,0:20:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.54,0:20:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But how do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.36,0:20:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Sh-She just saw some posters in the town!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.06,0:20:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.82,0:20:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, it looks delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.28,0:20:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.24,0:21:02.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,I hope Jimmy is still there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.83,0:21:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Where are you going, Pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.53,0:21:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Something came up. {chotto ne = somwhere for a moment}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.70,0:21:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Going first! {osaki ni = let me go first/take the fast lane}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.34,0:21:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.77,0:21:11.22,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Going first!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.37,0:21:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.92,0:21:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.99,0:22:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! A keychain! {/keyholder}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.14,0:22:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was for Jimmy. {??}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.03,0:22:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.96,0:22:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously? We all bought the same? {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.68,0:23:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel, why does Sheila \Nkeep boasting about being rich?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.15,0:23:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, and I wonder \Nwhy she decided to behave that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.66,0:23:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mother is a very down-to-earth person, \Nbut Sheila is the complete opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.31,0:23:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She must not be right in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.06,0:23:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was especially bad today, \Nwith even Janet finally erupting with rage. {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.14,0:23:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I've had enough of this fuss!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.64,0:23:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.39,0:24:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sheila's Secret."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.39,0:24:03.86,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 9 \NSheila's Secret {シェイラの秘密}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.71,0:24:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
